---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Dorian Insights — Making Your Data and Decisions Simpler"
  description="Dorian Insights makes your data and your decisions simpler — guiding executives and business owners from complicated, unreliable analytics to clear, trusted answers. Schedule a call."
>

<!-- =========================================================== -->
<!-- HERO — the customer's desire, and one clear next step        -->
<!-- =========================================================== -->
<header class="hero" id="top">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="eyebrow reveal">Senior Data &amp; Analytics Consulting</span>
    <h1 class="reveal">
      Your data, made simpler. <span class="quiet">Your decisions, made easier.</span>
    </h1>
    <div class="hero-body">
      <div class="reveal">
        <p class="lede">
          You've invested in data and analytics — but somewhere along the way it all got complicated, and the answers still aren't there when you need them. Let us help you - Dorian Insights makes your data and your decisions simpler and more reliable. We guide leaders and decision-makers from complexity and doubt to clear, trusted answers.
        </p>
        <div class="cta-row">
          <a class="btn-primary" href="#contact">Schedule a call <span>→</span></a>
          <a class="btn-secondary" href="#plan">See how it works</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <aside class="hero-stat-card reveal">
        <p>If your data isn't delivering, you're not alone. Only <strong>24%</strong> of Fortune 1000 companies describe themselves as data-driven — and <strong>78%</strong> say the barriers are human: culture, people, and process, not technology. The problem is common. Staying stuck doesn't have to be.</p>
        <div class="src">Wavestone · NewVantage · Gartner</div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<!-- =========================================================== -->
<!-- PROBLEM — external, internal, philosophical, and the stakes  -->
<!-- =========================================================== -->
<section id="problem">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <div class="section-marker">The Problem</div>
      <div class="section-title">
        <h2>Somewhere along the way, <span class="quiet">data got complicated.</span></h2>
        <p class="deck">Most leaders we speak with aren't short on data. They're buried in complexity and short on answers they can trust.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="problems-grid reveal-stagger">
      <article class="problem">
        <h3>The numbers don't agree</h3>
        <p>Dashboards contradict each other, reports arrive late, and every meeting starts with a debate about whose figures are right.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="problem">
        <h3>Every decision feels like a gamble</h3>
        <p>When you can't trust the data, you fall back on gut feel — and carry the quiet stress of hoping you guessed right.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="problem">
        <h3>It shouldn't be this complicated</h3>
        <p>You've paid for the tools and the people. A business that invests in data deserves simple, reliable answers — not more moving parts.</p>
      </article>
    </div>

    <p class="outcomes-footnote reveal">And the longer it stays this way, the more it costs: slow decisions, costly delays, missed opportunities — and competitors who move first.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- =========================================================== -->
<!-- SUCCESS — paint the picture of life after                    -->
<!-- =========================================================== -->
<section id="outcomes">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <div class="section-marker">What Success Looks Like</div>
      <div class="section-title">
        <h2>Imagine <span class="quiet">this becoming your default.</span></h2>
        <p class="deck">This is the shift from overwhelmed to empowered — from complicated to simple.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="outcomes-grid reveal-stagger">
      <article class="outcome">
        <p>Your executive team walks into every strategy meeting with <strong>trusted, up-to-date answers</strong> — no debates about the numbers, just decisions.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="outcome">
        <p>Your data from every system is organized, unified, and <strong>AI-ready</strong> in a single central platform.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="outcome">
        <p>Your next strategic bet is informed by <strong>data your competitors simply don't have</strong>.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="outcome">
        <p>Your technical and business teams speak a <strong>common language</strong> — pulling in the same direction, talking to each other rather than at each other.</p>
      </article>
    </div>

    <p class="outcomes-footnote reveal">These outcomes aren't hypothetical. They're what our engagements are designed to deliver — and what your team keeps long after we're gone.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- =========================================================== -->
<!-- GUIDE — empathy first, then authority                        -->
<!-- =========================================================== -->
<section id="guide">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <div class="section-marker">Your Guide</div>
      <div class="section-title">
        <h2>You know your business. <span class="quiet">We know how to make your data serve it.</span></h2>
        <p class="deck">You don't need another vendor selling a platform. You need a guide who has walked this road before — and who puts your team in the lead.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="about-grid">
      <div class="essay reveal">
        <p>We understand how frustrating it is to invest heavily in analytics and still walk into the boardroom without answers you trust. We've sat on both sides of that table — inside Fortune 500 organizations and alongside smaller, scrappier teams — and we've seen that the problem is rarely the technology. It's the connection between <strong>data, decisions, and people</strong> — and the complexity that builds up around it. Our job is to make all of it simpler.</p>
        <p>Dorian Insights distills two decades of experience — at Tier 1 consulting firms and inside multiple Fortune 500 clients, across strategy, data platforms, and AI — into a senior-principal practice. You work directly with the person doing the work: big-picture strategy and hands-on technical depth from the same chair, with none of the overhead.</p>
        <p>And the goal is never dependence. We build durable, in-house capability — <strong>your team owns the results</strong> long after the engagement ends.</p>

        <div class="about-stats">
          <div class="stat">
            <div class="num">20+</div>
            <div class="label">Years guiding technology &amp; data decisions</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat">
            <div class="num">F500</div>
            <div class="label">Multiple Fortune 500 engagements delivered</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat">
            <div class="num">Tier 1</div>
            <div class="label">Consulting firm leadership background</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat">
            <div class="num">Multiple</div>
            <div class="label">Technology and data stacks (e.g. Snowflake, BigQuery)</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="principal-card reveal">
        <div class="label">Why leaders choose us</div>
        <h3>What you get</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Complexity removed, not added — simpler is the deliverable</li>
          <li>Senior expertise on your problem — never delegated down</li>
          <li>Practical, accountable AI — only where it moves your needle</li>
          <li>Plain language between your business and technical teams</li>
          <li>Low overhead and flexible engagement, on your terms</li>
          <li>Your team enabled and upskilled, not replaced</li>
        </ul>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- =========================================================== -->
<!-- PLAN — three simple steps                                    -->
<!-- =========================================================== -->
<section id="plan">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <div class="section-marker">The Plan</div>
      <div class="section-title">
        <h2>Three simple steps <span class="quiet">to simpler data and easier decisions.</span></h2>
        <p class="deck">No mysterious methodology — simplicity starts with how we work. A clear path from where you are to where you want to be.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="plan-grid reveal-stagger">
      <article class="plan-step">
        <div class="step-num">1</div>
        <h3>Schedule a call</h3>
        <p>A 30-minute conversation to assess where your analytics stand today — what's working, what isn't, and why.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="plan-step">
        <div class="step-num">2</div>
        <h3>Get your roadmap</h3>
        <p>Together we develop a tailored plan in plain language, tied to business outcomes — not a technology wish list.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="plan-step">
        <div class="step-num">3</div>
        <h3>Move forward with confidence</h3>
        <p>Kick off your data transformation with a senior guide beside you — and watch decisions get faster, easier, and better grounded.</p>
      </article>
    </div>

    <div class="plan-cta reveal">
      <a class="btn-primary" href="#contact">Schedule a call <span>→</span></a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- =========================================================== -->
<!-- SERVICES                                                     -->
<!-- =========================================================== -->
<section id="services">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <div class="section-marker">Services</div>
      <div class="section-title">
        <h2>How we help <span class="quiet">you get there.</span></h2>
        <p class="deck">Every service exists for one reason: making your data — and the decisions that depend on it — simpler and more trustworthy. Most engagements draw from more than one, depending on what's currently blocking your progress.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="services-grid reveal-stagger">
      <article class="service feature">
        <div class="feature-grid">
          <div>
            <span class="num">AI / LLM integration &amp; automation</span>
            <h3>AI that actually moves your needle</h3>
            <p class="desc">Bringing language models and AI into your analytical workflow — practically, accountably, and only where they genuinely help your business.</p>
          </div>
          <ul>
            <li>AI-ready data foundations</li>
            <li>SQL and Python generation and review</li>
            <li>Integration with automated testing</li>
            <li>PR review and commentary</li>
            <li>Documentation that improves LLM performance</li>
            <li>Team upskilling &amp; change management</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="service">
        <span class="num">Strategy</span>
        <h3>Decisions connected to data</h3>
        <p class="desc">Connecting metrics to business outcomes. Translating technical reality into language your leadership team can act on.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Decision &amp; question framing</li>
          <li>Non-technical and technical stakeholder communication</li>
          <li>Business case development</li>
          <li>Stakeholder alignment &amp; communication</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="service">
        <span class="num">Operations &amp; Team</span>
        <h3>Your effort turned into output</h3>
        <p class="desc">Structure, process, and software development best practices that turn your high-effort analytics team into a high-output one.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Team structure, hiring, and standards</li>
          <li>Stakeholder communication &amp; facilitation</li>
          <li>Roadmaps, prioritization, and requirements</li>
          <li>Cognitive offload for senior leaders</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="service">
        <span class="num">Platform &amp; cost</span>
        <h3>A platform that scales, at a cost you can defend</h3>
        <p class="desc">Cloud data warehouse architecture, expansion, and rightsizing — built to grow with you without becoming a line item nobody can explain.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Cloud data platform architecture evaluation and implementation (e.g. Snowflake, BigQuery)</li>
          <li>AWS, Azure, and GCP implementation, evaluation, and usage within analytics workflows</li>
          <li>Cost engineering and complexity management</li>
          <li>Platform security &amp; access design</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="service">
        <span class="num">Modeling &amp; code quality</span>
        <h3>Numbers your whole company agrees on</h3>
        <p class="desc">Applying proven software engineering discipline to your analytics — so the answers are simple, consistent, tested, and maintainable.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Dimensional modeling &amp; grain definition</li>
          <li>dbt, SQL, and Python project audits and refactors</li>
          <li>Cost profiling and query optimization</li>
          <li>Testing frameworks, generation, and documentation</li>
          <li>Scalable and manageable data pipeline design and implementation (e.g. DAGs)</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- =========================================================== -->
<!-- ENGAGEMENT                                                   -->
<!-- =========================================================== -->
<section id="engagement">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <div class="section-marker">Engagement</div>
      <div class="section-title">
        <h2>Three ways <span class="quiet">to work together.</span></h2>
        <p class="deck">You choose the shape that matches what you need now. Engagements can — and often do — change form as the work evolves.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="models-grid reveal-stagger">
      <article class="model">
        <div class="tag">Fractional retainer</div>
        <h3>Embedded senior presence</h3>
        <p class="summary">Ongoing committed hours — consistent senior leadership without a full-time hire.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Dedicated weekly hours reserved for your engagement</li>
          <li>Predictable monthly investment, billed against committed hours</li>
          <li>Highest priority access and continuity</li>
          <li>Minimum 3-month term; preferred rates at longer terms</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="best-for">
          <strong>Best for</strong>
          ongoing leadership needs — data team leadership, platform stewardship, embedded principal architect.
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="model">
        <div class="tag">Project-based</div>
        <h3>Defined scope, defined outcome</h3>
        <p class="summary">Time and materials against clearly defined deliverables and milestones.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Scope, milestones, acceptance criteria agreed upfront</li>
          <li>Proposals include timeline and investment range</li>
          <li>Scope adapts as findings surface — data work always surprises</li>
          <li>Honest re-baselining when the work calls for it</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="best-for">
          <strong>Best for</strong>
          specific initiatives — platform builds, dbt overhauls, cost optimization, modernization roadmaps.
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="model">
        <div class="tag">Advisory</div>
        <h3>Targeted, burst availability</h3>
        <p class="summary">Block of hours for architecture reviews, ad hoc analysis, or advisory calls.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Hourly or block-of-hours, purchased in advance or monthly</li>
          <li>Typical block: 10–20 hours used over 4–8 weeks</li>
          <li>No long-term commitment required</li>
          <li>Scheduling subject to current availability</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="best-for">
          <strong>Best for</strong>
          targeted, flexible engagements — second opinions, decision support, short-form analysis.
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- =========================================================== -->
<!-- SELECTED WORK — proof the guide delivers                     -->
<!-- =========================================================== -->
<section id="work" class="work-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <div class="section-marker">Results</div>
      <div class="section-title">
        <h2>Teams that <span class="quiet">stopped guessing.</span></h2>
        <p class="deck">In every engagement the client's team is the hero — our job is to hand them the map. A few representative examples.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="work-list reveal-stagger">
      <article class="work-item">
        <div class="work-meta">
          <div class="industry">Major Airline</div>
          <div class="stack">Snowflake · Near real-time flight analytics</div>
          <div class="tags">
            <span>Modeling</span>
            <span>Performance</span>
            <span>Executive</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="work-body">
          <p>An operations team that now trusts its numbers: seven years and roughly fifteen billion rows of behavioral data modeled, transformed, and validated into a governed analytics layer they rely on daily.</p>
          <p>Near-real-time turn analysis across 40+ event types, sourced from 20+ systems, supporting more than a thousand flights per day. Extensive tuning and cost/query plan work drove compute spend down materially.</p>
          <p>Findings presented directly to the C-suite to inform scheduling, reliability, and revenue decisions.</p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="work-item">
        <div class="work-meta">
          <div class="industry">Technology Consultancy</div>
          <div class="stack">BigQuery · FP&amp;A KPI Platform</div>
          <div class="tags">
            <span>Platform</span>
            <span>ML</span>
            <span>Operations</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="work-body">
          <p>A leadership team running the whole business from numbers it trusts: a BigQuery-based analytics platform reconciling leads, revenue, profitability, and staffing across four core source systems.</p>
          <p>A 200+ node modeled project, including capture of historical change over time. Up-to-the-hour KPIs delivered to leadership; in-database ML used to forecast revenue direction and inform staffing investment.</p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="work-item">
        <div class="work-meta">
          <div class="industry">Major Entertainment Firm</div>
          <div class="stack">Snowflake · Cost &amp; Production Analytics</div>
          <div class="tags">
            <span>Production</span>
            <span>Governance</span>
            <span>Renegotiation</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="work-body">
          <p>A production organization that renegotiated from a position of knowledge: a Snowflake-based analytics platform for episodic production, staffing, and cost analysis spanning multiple concurrent productions and third-party vendors.</p>
          <p>Findings led to fundamental renegotiation of project structure, payroll, accounting, and operations with third-party firms — and drove re-examination of production locations, staffing duplication, and governance of accounting and data quality.</p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- =========================================================== -->
<!-- CONTACT — the direct call to action                          -->
<!-- =========================================================== -->
<section id="contact" class="contact">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="eyebrow reveal">Schedule a Call</span>
    <h2 class="reveal">Ready to make your data — <span class="quiet">and your decisions — simpler?</span></h2>
    <p class="lede reveal">Tell us what's gotten too complicated. In 30 minutes you'll know whether we can help and what the first step looks like — no pressure, no obligation.</p>

    <!-- Google Calendar Appointment Scheduling button -->
    <div class="contact-booking reveal">
      <link href="https://calendar.google.com/calendar/scheduling-button-script.css" rel="stylesheet">
      <script is:inline src="https://calendar.google.com/calendar/scheduling-button-script.js" async></script>
      <script is:inline>
      (function() {
        var target = document.currentScript;
        window.addEventListener('load', function() {
          calendar.schedulingButton.load({
            url: 'https://calendar.google.com/calendar/appointments/schedules/AcZssZ2yZAt4o1tI0kNiuIGW5iHlMNpJpkZ7GZTIgVB6OPQAb4NPMPqy3JndE92pA-ckX_7vWvsflC_8?gv=true',
            color: '#1B1464',
            label: 'Schedule a call',
            target: target,
          });
        });
      })();
      </script>
    </div>

    <p class="contact-divider reveal"><span>not ready for a call? send a message instead</span></p>

    <form
      class="contact-form reveal"
      name="contact"
      method="POST"
      action="/thanks/"
      data-netlify="true"
      data-netlify-honeypot="bot-field"
    >
      <input type="hidden" name="form-name" value="contact">
      <p class="hp"><label>Don't fill this out if you're human: <input name="bot-field"></label></p>

      <div class="field-row">
        <div class="field">
          <label for="contact-name">Name</label>
          <input id="contact-name" type="text" name="name" required autocomplete="name">
        </div>
        <div class="field">
          <label for="contact-email-input">Email</label>
          <input id="contact-email-input" type="email" name="email" required autocomplete="email">
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="field">
        <label for="contact-company">Company <span class="optional">(optional)</span></label>
        <input id="contact-company" type="text" name="company" autocomplete="organization">
      </div>

      <div class="field">
        <label for="contact-message">What's not working with your data today?</label>
        <textarea id="contact-message" name="message" rows="5" required></textarea>
      </div>

      <button class="btn-primary" type="submit">Send message <span>→</span></button>

      <p class="contact-form-foot">
        Or email <a href="mailto:hello@dorianinsights.com">hello@dorianinsights.com</a> directly,
        or connect on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/joshuaroyandrews/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>.
      </p>
    </form>

    <div class="colophon">
      <div>
        <span class="label">Practice</span>
        Dorian Insights, L.L.C.
      </div>
      <div>
        <span class="label">Focus</span>
        Data · Analytics · Strategy · Architecture
      </div>
      <div>
        <span class="label">Engagement</span>
        Fractional · Project · Advisory
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</Base>
